Explain the difference between the dfs() function and the bfs() function.


The dfs() function is a depth-first search algorithm, which means it explores the deepest possible path in the graph before backtracking to find other paths. On the other hand, the bfs() function is a breadth-first search algorithm, which means it explores the nearest possible paths in the graph before exploring deeper paths.

